docs.abstract: Former executives at the tech giant give an inside account of its management culture in a new book.
docs.snippet: Former executives at the tech giant give an inside account of its management culture in a new book.
docs.lead_paragraph: The DealBook newsletter delves into a single topic or theme every weekend. With Jeff Bezos preparing to step down from Amazon, today take a look at the culture of the company he founded through the prism of a new book by two former executives at the e-commerce giant. We’ll soon see whether the practices Mr. Bezos developed live on, or go out the door with him.

docs.abstract: The Amazon founder prepares to step back just as Washington turns up the heat on the mega-retailer and cloud company.
docs.snippet: The Amazon founder prepares to step back just as Washington turns up the heat on the mega-retailer and cloud company.
docs.lead_paragraph: If I had to guess who inspired Amazon’s founder, Jeff Bezos, to kick himself upstairs and appoint Andy Jassy, a deputy, as his successor as chief executive, I might wager that at least part of the blame can be laid on Lucy McBath, the freshman Georgia congresswoman, and her understated grilling of one of the world’s richest men at a July hearing held by the House antitrust subcommittee.
